children.subject:
Students planning to apply for the masters' programs are the reason that it's only unlikely and not impossible.  My suggestion would be to prioritize getting into the undergrad section of the class and then approach Michael Sun once you're in that class. If he vouches for you, as long as the instructor is ok, we'll move you into the 2xxA course.

By doing so, you would be committed to applying for the masters program.
Just wondering but are 186 and 286A the same course? Or how are the ugrad and grad classes different

They are the same course. 186 is for undergrads to enroll in, while 286A is for grads. The graduate version usually requires some extra component/work. Both 186 and 286A have the same lectures, discussions, etc.
